# Starters Unit Authoring (U1–U10)

**Read first:** `scripts/lib/starters-blueprints/TEMPLATE.md`

**Gold reference (Unit 1):** `scripts/lib/starters-blueprints/unit-01/` + `shared/family-and-friends-content.mjs`

**Curriculum:** `data/curriculum/cambridge-curriculum-map.json` → `levels.starters.units[N-1]`

## When user asks to create Starters U2–U10

1. Read the unit brief from the curriculum map (slug, title, vocabulary, grammar, readingSkill, listeningSkill).
2. Copy **structure** from Unit 1 — never copy Family and Friends **content**.
3. Create `shared/<slug>-content.mjs` + `unit-0N.mjs` + `unit-0N/*.mjs` (6 skills).
4. Target: **18 lessons × 90 exercises** (5 per lesson: Learn, Practice, Check, Apply, Review).
5. Reuse character **Mai (8)** across Starters units for continuity.
6. Only **Check** exercises use AI `writing` / `speaking`.
7. Review exercises must be **hand-crafted**, not duplicates of Check.
8. All `explanation` fields in **Vietnamese** with pedagogical distractor notes on MCQ.
9. `topicTag` = unit slug; `levelTag` = `"starters"`.

## Pipeline (run in order)

```bash
node scripts/generate-cambridge-units.mjs starters <N>
npm run validate:starters
npm run generate:listening-audio -- starters <N>
npm run seed:starters -- --from <N> --to <N> --unlock-test-student
```

## Shared code (do not fork)

- `scripts/lib/cambridge-unit-builder.mjs` — Starters meta: Pre-A1, minWords 5, speaking 60s
- `scripts/lib/starters-blueprints/shared/exercise-helpers.mjs` — `createStartersFactory()`
- `sentence_ordering`: use `items` + `correctOrder`

## Scope boundary

- **In scope:** Starters units 1–10
- **Out of scope:** Movers, Flyers, KET, PET — each has its own blueprint folder

See also: `.cursor/rules/unit-content-authoring.mdc` for JSON quality rules.
